text: Ordered 1 for 1 Frasers kaya butter toast set, asked what drink in the set I could get, male cashier gave the option of honey lemon. Bill ended up to be $7.80. 2 drinks costed additional $2.20. He did not tell me there was additional charge for honey lemon and did not ask if I wanted hot or cold.

Their breakfast set is very cost-effective, the coffee is very fragrant, and the braised noodles taste very good. What I like most is that they are very enthusiastic towards every guest, so I really like coming here. The price is affordable! ! Give it a thumbs up! !
I went to eat Laksa and it tasted delicious. The kopi was also delicious. The service attitude was very good. I was very satisfied with my purchase.
